An auto crash has claimed the lives of a family of five in Akure Ondo State. The victims, a father, mother, and their three children lost their lives when the car they were riding in rammed into a stationary heavy-duty truck, Daily Post reports. The accident occurred around 10:00 pm on Tuesday in the Oluwatuyi area of the Ijoka axis. -Advertisement- The man, who was said to have driven an Akure taxi-painted car with his family, was headed home from the Shoprite area along Ijo-Mimo road, which is under construction when they met their untimely death. According to sources, the driver was at high speed when the accident occurred. An eyewitness, who is also a taxi driver, stated that there was no way the deceased would not have seen such a huge truck. He went on to say that the motorist must have been driving at high speed, exacerbating the impact of the collision and that he was under the influence of alcohol. He claimed that while they tried to recover their remains, the man reeked of alcohol. Meanwhile, the Police Public Relations Officer, PPRO, SP Fumilayo Odunlami, confirmed the incident.